| NCSC Exercise in a Box | Free cyberattack simulation exercises | ncsc.gov.uk/information/exercise-in-a-box |

---

## Tools Not Recommended (and Why)

**LastPass:** Suffered a significant breach in 2022 where encrypted password vaults were stolen. While the encryption means direct access to passwords requires cracking the master password, the breach fundamentally undermined trust. Bitwarden or 1Password are better choices.

**Free VPNs:** Many free VPN services log your traffic and sell the data — the opposite of what you want. If you need a VPN (for working on public WiFi), use a paid reputable service (Mullvad, ProtonVPN) or just use mobile data instead, which is simpler.

**"All-in-one security suites" from unfamiliar vendors:** Products that promise antivirus + VPN + identity protection + dark web monitoring + backup in one cheap package often do all of these poorly. Use dedicated tools for each purpose.

---

*Part of the Small Business Information Security Starter Kit. Tool pricing and availability correct as of early 2025. Check current pricing directly with providers.*
